<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/10ffddd3573588a757dd24d7a31e7c0c.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 10 and A = 5 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>114.3</li><li>114.7</li><li>85.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({5}\right)}}}=\frac{{10}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{10}}{{\tan{{\left({5}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{114.30052302761}\approx{114.3}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={10}^{{2}}+{114.30052302761}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={100}+{13064.609564386}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={13164.609564386}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{13164.609564386}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{114.7371324567}\approx{114.7}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{5}^{\circ}\approx{85}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

